code:
# Built by Seazon - Join our Discord: https://discord.gg/rx3H3m39AX

on join :
  set {_player} to the player

  # Check if the player has the required permission
  if not has permission {_player} "teleport.random":
    send "&cYou do not have permission to use this command!"
    cancel event
  end

  # Teleport the player to a random location
  teleport {_player} to a random location between 0 and 1000 on the x-axis, 0 and 1000 on the y-axis, and 0 and 1000 on the z-axis

on command "/tp-random":
  set {_player} to the player who executed the command

  # Check if the player has the required permission
  if not has permission {_player} "teleport.random":
    send "&cYou do not have permission to use this command!"
    return
  end

  # Get the destination coordinates from the player
  set {_x} to the argument 1 of the command
  set {_y} to the argument 2 of the command
  set {_z} to the argument 3 of the command

  # Check if the player provided the destination coordinates
  if not {_x} is a number and {_y} is a number and {_z} is a number:
    send "&cPlease provide x, y, and z coordinates as arguments!"
    return
  end

  # Teleport the player to the specified location
  teleport {_player} to {_x}, {_y}, {_z}

  # Send a confirmation message to the player
  send "&aYou have been teleported to ({_x}, {_y}, {_z})"

on disable :
  # Save the last used coordinates to a file
  set {_file} to "last-teleport-location.yml"
  save {_file} to "{x: {player-x}, y: {player-y}, z: {player-z}}"

  # Load the last used coordinates from the file
  set {_lastLocation} to load {_file}
  if {_lastLocation} is not null:
    # Teleport the player to the last used location
    teleport {_player} to {_lastLocation.x}, {_lastLocation.y}, {_lastLocation.z}
  end

# Define a function to generate a random location
function getRandomLocation():
  return random location between 0 and 1000 on the x-axis, 0 and 1000 on the y-axis, and 0 and 1000 on the z-axis

# Define a variable to store the last used coordinates
variable last-teleport-location: file

# Define a variable to store the player's current coordinates
variable player-teleport-location: location

on load:
  # Initialize variables

  location = loc(0, 0, 0)

  # Set random teleportation range

  # Define teleportation function
  function teleport-player:
    # Get random location within teleport-range
    rand-loc = loc(rand(-teleport-range, teleport-range), rand(0, 200), rand(-teleport-range, teleport-range))
    
    # Teleport player to random location
    player.teleport(rand-loc)

  # Register teleportation function to player
  player.on move:
    # Teleport player to random location every 5 seconds
    delay 5:
      teleport-player

on close:
  # Unregister teleportation function to prevent memory leak
  player.unregister-commands()

name: make a voting reward
code:
# Built by Seazon - Join our Discord: https://discord.gg/rx3H3m39AX

# Voting Rewards Skript
# Version: 1.0
# Description: Rewards players with items based on their vote count

# Import necessary libraries
import craftbukkit
import skript

# Define configuration options
config:
  # Set the reward items
  reward-items:
    - id: minecraft:emerald
      amount: 5
    - id: minecraft:gold_ore
      amount: 3
  # Set the vote threshold
  vote-threshold: 10
  # Set the maximum reward
  max-reward: 100

# Define the VotingRewards class
class VotingRewards {
  # Initialize the class
  init:
    # Load the configuration
    load-config()
    
    # Register the on-player-join event
    register-event player-join "onPlayerJoin"
    
    # Register the on-player-vote event
    register-event player-vote "onPlayerVote"
    
    # Register the on-tick event
    register-event tick "onTick"
  
  # Load the configuration from the config.yml file
  load-config:
    # Load the reward items
    reward-items:
      - id: $(config.reward-items)[0].id
        amount: $(config.reward-items)[0].amount
    - id: $(config.reward-items)[1].id
      amount: $(config.reward-items)[1].amount
    # Load the vote threshold and maximum reward
    vote-threshold: $(config.vote-threshold)
    max-reward: $(config.max-reward)
  
  # Handle the on-player-join event
  onPlayerJoin:
    # Get the joining player
    player: event-player
    
    # Check if the player has voted before
    if player.has-tag "voted":
      # Clear the player's vote count
      player.remove-tag "voted"
    
    # Set the player's vote count to 0
    player.set-tag "votes", 0
  
  # Handle the on-player-vote event
  onPlayerVote:
    # Get the voting player
    player: event-player
    
    # Get the player's vote count
    vote-count: player.get-tag "votes"
    
    # Increment the player's vote count
    player.set-tag "votes", vote-count + 1
    
    # Check if the player has reached the vote threshold
    if vote-count >= $(config.vote-threshold):
      # Reward the player with items
      reward-player(player)
  
  # Handle the on-tick event
  onTick:
    # Check if the player has reached the maximum reward
    for player in craftbukkit.get-online-players():
      vote-count: player.get-tag "votes"
      max-reward: $(config.max-reward)
      
      # Check if the player has reached the maximum reward
      if vote-count >= max-reward:
        # Remove excess votes
        player.set-tag "votes", max-reward
      
      # Reward the player with items
      reward-player(player)
  
  # Reward a player with items
  reward-player(player):
    # Get the player's vote count
    vote-count: player.get-tag "votes"
    
    # Check if the player has reached the maximum reward
    max-reward: $(config.max-reward)
    if vote-count >= max-reward:
      # Do not reward the player
      return
    
    # Get the reward items
    reward-items: $(config.reward-items)
    
    # Loop through the reward items
    for item in reward-items:
      # Give the player the item
      player.give-item(item.id, item.amount)
  
  # Register the VotingRewards class
  register:
    VotingRewards()
}

# Voting Rewards Skript
# Author: [Your Name]
# Version: 1.0
# Minecraft Version: 1.20
# Skript Version: 2.8

# Import necessary Skript libraries
import crafttweaker.api.items.ItemStack
import crafttweaker.api.player.Player
import org.bukkit.Bukkit
import org.bukkit.entity.Player
import org.bukkit.event.EventHandler
import org.bukkit.event.Listener
import org.bukkit.event.player.PlayerJoinEvent
import org.bukkit.event.player.PlayerQuitEvent
import org.bukkit.event.player.PlayerVoteEvent

# Define a custom reward item
define reward item reward_item as {
    name: "Voting Reward"
    material: "PLAYER_HEAD"
    amount: 1
}

# Define a custom reward
define reward reward as {
    name: "Voting Reward"
    description: "Reward for voting for the server."
    item: reward_item
}

# Define a custom vote reward command
on command vote_reward:
    if sender is player:
        # Check if the player has voted for the server
        if player.hasPermission("voting_rewards.vote"):
            # Reward the player with the custom reward
            player.giveItem(reward_item)
            send "&aYou have been rewarded with &f{reward_item.name}!")
        else:
            send "&cYou do not have permission to vote for rewards.")

# Define a custom vote event listener
on event PlayerVoteEvent:
    # Check if the player has voted for the server
    if event.getVote() == "yes":
        # Reward the player with the custom reward
        player.giveItem(reward_item)
        send "&aPlayer &f{event.getPlayer().getDisplayName()} &ahas been rewarded with &f{reward_item.name}!")

# Define a custom on join event listener
on event PlayerJoinEvent:
    # Give the player a message about the voting rewards system
    send "&aWelcome to the server! &fYou can vote for rewards by using the &f/vote &areward command.")

# Define a custom on quit event listener
on event PlayerQuitEvent:
    # Give the player a message about the voting rewards system
    send "&aGoodbye &f{event.getPlayer().getDisplayName()}! &fYou can vote for rewards by using the &f/vote &areward command.")

# Random Teleport Plugin for Minecraft Skript

# Import necessary libraries
import craft.api
import math.random

# Define plugin settings
# Configuration options
teleport-delay: 10 # Delay between teleports in seconds
teleport-distance: 100 # Maximum teleport distance

# Define player variables
player-tp-target: player() # Target player for teleport
player-tp-destination: location() # Teleport destination

# Define event listeners
on join:
    # Initialize player variables when a player joins the server
    player-tp-target = player()
    player-tp-destination = random-location() # Set initial random location for player-tp-destination

on tick:
    # Check if a random teleport is due
    if time() % (teleport-delay * 20) == 0:
        # Teleport the player to a random location within the teleport-distance
        player-tp-target tp random-location(teleport-distance)

# Define custom functions
function random-location(max-distance):
    # Return a random location within the specified distance from the player's location
    x = math.random() * max-distance * 2 - max-distance
    y = math.random() * max-distance * 2 - max-distance
    z = math.random() * max-distance * 2 - max-distance
    return location(player().x + x, player().y + y, player().z + z)

# Define error handling
on error:
    # Log the error message
    echo "Error: " + error-message()

    # Check if the custom join message configuration exists

        # Display a default join message to the player

    else:

  else:

  # Set the configuration file's content

# Made from CodersLab - Join our Discord: https://discord.gg/FYv6kDJg3Y

# Discord Link Menu Skript
# Version: 1.0
# Author: Minecraft Development AI Assistant
# Description: A comprehensive Discord link menu skript for Minecraft servers.

# Import necessary libraries and load configurations
import discord
import json
load config from "discord_config.json"

# Define constants and variables
option discord_link: "https://discord.gg/your-server"
option discord_invite_code: "your-server"
option menu_title: "Join Our Discord Server!"
option menu_size: 5
option menu_items:
  - "Join Discord"
  - "View Invite Code"
  - "Copy Invite Link"
  - "Open Discord Website"
  - "Close Menu"

# Define menu functions
function discord_link_menu():
  # Create a new menu instance
  create menu instance "discord_link_menu" with size menu_size
  set menu title to menu_title

  # Add menu items
  add menu item "Join Discord" with command "/discord join"
  add menu item "View Invite Code" with command "/discord code"
  add menu item "Copy Invite Link" with command "/discord copy"
  add menu item "Open Discord Website" with command "/discord website"
  add menu item "Close Menu" with command "/discord close"

  # Display the menu to the player
  show menu "discord_link_menu" to player

# Define command handlers
command /discord:
  usage: /discord <join|code|copy|website|close>
  permission: discord.link
  permission message: "You do not have permission to use this command."

  # Join Discord command handler
  if arg 1 is "join":
    send message "Click this link to join our Discord server: %discord_link%" to player
    send action bar "Joining Discord server..." to player
    execute console command "discord join %player%" asynchronously

  # View Invite Code command handler
  if arg 1 is "code":
    send message "Our Discord invite code is: %discord_invite_code%" to player

  # Copy Invite Link command handler
  if arg 1 is "copy":
    copy text "%discord_link%" to player's clipboard
    send message "Discord invite link copied to clipboard!" to player

  # Open Discord Website command handler
  if arg 1 is "website":
    open url "https://discord.com/" to player

  # Close Menu command handler
  if arg 1 is "close":
    close menu "discord_link_menu" for player

# Define menu click event handler
on menu click:
  # Get the clicked menu item
  set clicked_item to clicked item

  # Handle menu item clicks
  if clicked_item is "Join Discord":
    execute command "/discord join" as player
  if clicked_item is "View Invite Code":
    execute command "/discord code" as player
  if clicked_item is "Copy Invite Link":
    execute command "/discord copy" as player
  if clicked_item is "Open Discord Website":
    execute command "/discord website" as player
  if clicked_item is "Close Menu":
    close menu "discord_link_menu" for player

# Define player join event handler
on player join:
  # Send a message to the player with the Discord link
  send message "Join our Discord server: %discord_link%" to player

# Define player quit event handler
on player quit:
  # Remove the player from the menu instance
  remove player from menu instance "discord_link_menu"
